A = (a_{ij})
1 \leq i \leq m
1 \leq j \leq n
m \times n
A: \mathbb{R}^n \to \mathbb{R}^m
 A(x) = A(x_1,...,x_n) = ( \sum_{j=1}^n a_{1j}x_j, ..., \sum_{j=1}^n a_{mj}x_j ) 
 ||A(x)||_{\infty} \leq C ||x||_{\infty}
C = \max\{ \sum_{j=1}^n |a_{ij}| : 1 \leq j \leq m \} 
||A(x)||
\|A(x)\|_\infty
A(x)
 A(x) = ( \sum_{j=1}^n a_{1j}x_j, ..., \sum_{j=1}^n a_{mj}x_j ) 
 \|A(x)\|_\infty = \max_{1 \leq k \leq m} \left|\sum_{j=1}^n a_{kj}x_j\right| 
l
1 \leq l \leq k
||A(x)|| = \left| \sum_{j=1}^n a_{lj} x_l \right| 
 \therefore \left| \sum_{j=1}^n a_{lj} x_l \right| = \left| \sum_{j=1}^n a_{lj} \right| \left|x_l \right| \leq \max_{1 \leq i \leq m} \{ \left| \sum_{j=1}^n a_{lj} \right| \} |x_l| \leq C ||x||_{\infty}
|x_l| \leq \max\{ |x_i| : 1 \leq i \leq n \} = ||x||_{\infty}
